[2] Ukraine: Ukrainian health officials reported an additional 2138 measles cases in the past week, up 15% from the previous week
Date: Wed 28 Nov 2018
Source: Outbreak News Today [edited]
http://outbreaknewstoday.com/ukraine-reports-another-2000-measles-cases-past-week-annual-total-tops-42000/


During the week ending 24 Nov 2018, 729 adults and 1409 children were confirmed to have measles. Since the beginning of 2018, the Center for Public Health of the Ministry of Health of Ukraine has reported 42 040 measles cases (15 864 adults and 26 176 children). Of this total, 15 people have died.

Lviv has reported the most cases with 8835, followed by Ivano-Frankivsk (4297), Transcarpathian (3979) and the Odessa region (2623). In the capital of Kyiv, 2556 cases were reported.

Health officials continue to encourage immunization; in fact, they call it a matter of national security, as the health of Ukrainians -- all together and everyone in particular -- depends on the level of vaccination coverage in the country. As of 1 Nov 2018, the number of children who received the 1st dose of the MMR [measles, mumps, and rubella] vaccine was 76.1%, and the percentage receiving 2 doses of MMR was 77.5%. In each region of Ukraine there are sufficiently high-quality and effective vaccines for planned and enhanced immunization.

[Byline: Robert Herriman]

