[5] Israel
Date: Wed 28 Nov 2018
Source: Outbreak News Today [abridged, edited]
http://outbreaknewstoday.com/israel-measles-outbreak-tops-2000/


In an update on the measles outbreak in Israel, health officials have reported 2040 cases nationally, according to an Algemeiner report. Health Ministry officials say cities with large Haredi populations suffered the highest number of measles cases.

Jerusalem has seen 874 cases, followed by 266 in Beit Shemesh and 149 in Tzfat. Tel Aviv has reported 52 cases to date. The Health Ministry's data showed that the vast majority of cases have been reported in children. At least one child has died. and a 3-week old baby has been hospitalized.

--
