[7] New York (Rockland County)
Date: 29 Nov 2018
Source: News 12 [abridged, edited]
http://westchester.news12.com/story/39556422/health-experts-highlight-3-locations-in-measles-exposure-investigation


Officials in Rockland County are alerting residents to 3 possible measles exposure locations as cases in the county continue to rise. They say the 83 confirmed measles cases have affected residents in Spring Valley, New Square and Monsey. Because of the county's small size, they say measles exposure could occur anywhere in Rockland. Officials have released a list of locations in Spring Valley and West Nyack that may have been exposed to measles -- see source URL above.

