[10] Chile ex Venezuela
Date: Wed 28 Nov 2018
Source: Radioagricultura [translated online, edited]
https://www.radioagricultura.cl/nacional/2018/11/28/seremi-de-salud-confirma-nuevo-caso-de-sarampion-en-chile.html

The regional health minister of the metropolitan region, Omar Caceres, confirmed that there is a new imported case of measles in our country. It is a minor of Venezuelan nationality who entered Chile by land. As explained by the health authority, the boy left his country for Chile on 12 Nov [2018], traveling with his mother through Colombia, Ecuador and Peru. The regional health minister added that the boy arrived in Chile on 19 Nov [2018], where he took a bus from Arica to Santiago.

[Byline: Bastian Ljubetic]

